  2. GAP CO-USAGE (Interval)
    Verified H = 175 (0.0s)

    Single gap usage (total across all paths & vertices):
      gap 1: 350
      gap 2: 378
      gap 3: 322

    Co-usage matrix (normalized by H):
         g= 1 g= 2 g= 3
    g= 1  6.00  3.44  2.56
    g= 2  3.44  6.40  3.12
    g= 3  2.56  3.12  5.36

  3. WALSH COEFFICIENTS
    Degree-2 coefficients:
      h[{0,1}] =    +3.50  (chords with gaps 1,2 or 6,5)
      h[{0,2}] =    -3.50  (chords with gaps 1,3 or 6,4)
      h[{1,2}] =    -3.50  (chords with gaps 2,3 or 5,4)

  4. WALSH-USAGE CONNECTION
    For chord pair (i,j), define:
      U_(1, 2) = co-usage when both chords 'positive' (gap=i+1, j+1)
      V_(1, 2) = co-usage when both chords 'negative' (gap=p-i-1, p-j-1)
      W_(1, 2) = co-usage when mixed (one + one -)
    Walsh coeff h[{i,j}] should be related to (U+V-2W)/4

    chord pair (0,1): h_hat =  +3.50
      gaps: pos=(1,2), neg=(6,5)
      U=3.4400, V=0.0000, W=0.0000
      (U+V-2W)/4 = 0.8600

    chord pair (0,2): h_hat =  -3.50
      gaps: pos=(1,3), neg=(6,4)
      U=2.5600, V=0.0000, W=0.0000
      (U+V-2W)/4 = 0.6400

    chord pair (1,2): h_hat =  -3.50
      gaps: pos=(2,3), neg=(5,4)
      U=3.1200, V=0.0000, W=0.0000
      (U+V-2W)/4 = 0.7800


